<H1>Changing transfer authorisation for a host</H1>

<P>You can also use the <STRONG>hhstore</STRONG> command to remove the stored
authorisation for a host whenever you change your password.</P>

<P>For example:</P>

<PRE WIDTH=80>   <STRONG>hhstore -r festival</STRONG>
</PRE>

<P>This removes any access authorisation that you might have
stored for the host "festival".</P>

<P>Use of the <SAMP>-r</SAMP> option indicates that you want to remove the
current authorisation for a host.</P>

